 {"id":"bd-3vbf.3","title":"Design System: Pre-computed SemanticStyles Struct","description":"## Background

beads_viewer pre-computes style objects at startup rather than creating them per-frame:
```go
type ThemeStyles struct {
    StatusOpen      lipgloss.Style
    StatusOpenBadge lipgloss.Style  // fg + bg combo
    PriorityP0      lipgloss.Style
    PriorityP0Badge lipgloss.Style
    MutedText       lipgloss.Style
    InfoBold        lipgloss.Style
    // ...
}
```

This provides:
1. **Performance**: No per-frame style allocation
2. **Consistency**: Single source of truth for each semantic style
3. **Convenience**: Easy to use throughout codebase

## Implementation

```rust
pub struct SemanticStyles {
    // Status styles
    pub status_open: Style,
    pub status_open_badge: Style,
    pub status_progress: Style,
    pub status_progress_badge: Style,
    pub status_blocked: Style,
    pub status_blocked_badge: Style,
    pub status_closed: Style,

    // Priority styles
    pub priority_critical: Style,
    pub priority_critical_badge: Style,
    pub priority_high: Style,
    pub priority_high_badge: Style,
    pub priority_medium: Style,
    pub priority_low: Style,

    // Common semantic styles
    pub muted: Style,
    pub info: Style,
    pub info_bold: Style,
    pub success: Style,
    pub warning: Style,
    pub error: Style,
    pub link: Style,
    pub code: Style,
    pub kbd: Style,  // Keyboard key style
}

impl Default for SemanticStyles {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            status_open: Style::new().fg(status::OPEN).bold(),
            status_open_badge: Style::new().fg(bg::BASE).bg(status::OPEN).bold(),
            // ...
        }
    }
}
```

