-{"id":"bd-3vbf.31","title":"Testing Infrastructure: Unit Tests and E2E Scripts for Visual Polish","description":"## Background

AGENTS.md treats testing as critical, and visual polish work is easy to regress. This bead consolidates the **testing infrastructure** plus the **final snapshot update workflow** so everything is self-contained and deterministic.

## Scope

1. **Unit tests** for new theme/color/spacing/semantic-style code.
2. **Snapshot tests + blessing workflow** after visual changes.
3. **E2E scripts with verbose logging** for reproducibility.
4. **Debug logging hooks** for visual components (feature-gated).

---

## Phase A — Infrastructure (can start early)

### Theme/Color/Spacing Tests
```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod theme_tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn semantic_colors_have_valid_contrast() {
        // WCAG AA requires 4.5:1 contrast ratio
        assert!(contrast_ratio(status::OPEN, bg::BASE) >= 4.5);
        assert!(contrast_ratio(status::BLOCKED, bg::BASE) >= 4.5);
        assert!(contrast_ratio(priority::CRITICAL, bg::BASE) >= 4.5);
    }

    #[test]
    fn spacing_tokens_are_ordered() {
        assert!(spacing::XS < spacing::SM);
        assert!(spacing::SM < spacing::MD);
        assert!(spacing::MD < spacing::LG);
        assert!(spacing::LG < spacing::XL);
    }

    #[test]
    fn pre_computed_styles_are_valid() {
        let styles = SemanticStyles::default();
        assert!(styles.status_open.fg().is_some());
        assert!(styles.status_open_badge.bg().is_some());
    }
}
```

### Widget Tests (examples)
```rust
#[test]
fn sparkline_normalizes_correctly() {
    let data = vec![0.0, 50.0, 100.0];
    let spark = Sparkline::new(&data);
    let rendered = spark.render_string();
    assert_eq!(rendered.chars().count(), 3);
    assert!(rendered.contains('▁') || rendered.contains(' '));
    assert!(rendered.contains('█'));
}

#[test]
fn mini_bar_color_thresholds() {
    assert_eq!(MiniBar::color_for_value(0.80), status::SUCCESS);
    assert_eq!(MiniBar::color_for_value(0.60), status::WARNING);
    assert_eq!(MiniBar::color_for_value(0.30), accent::INFO);
    assert_eq!(MiniBar::color_for_value(0.10), fg::MUTED);
}

#[test]
fn status_badge_renders_correctly() {
    let badge = render_status_badge(Status::Open);
    assert!(badge.content.contains("OPEN"));
    assert!(badge.style.fg().is_some());
    assert!(badge.style.bg().is_some());
}
```

### Diagram Tests (markdown screen)
```rust
#[test]
fn diagram_detection_identifies_ascii_art() {
    let diagram = "+---+\n|   |\n+---+";
    assert!(is_likely_diagram(diagram));

    let text = "Hello world";
    assert!(!is_likely_diagram(text));
}

#[test]
fn diagram_correction_aligns_borders() {
    let input = "+------+\n| Hi|\n| Hello |\n+------+";
    let output = correct_diagram(input);
    let widths: Vec<usize> = output.lines().map(visual_width).collect();
    assert!(widths.windows(2).all(|w| w[0] == w[1]));
}
```

---

## Phase B — Snapshot Update & Visual Regression (do **last**)

### When
After the big visual changes land, especially:
- Dashboard overhaul
- Chrome: status bar + tab bar
- Any screen with layout/palette changes

### Process (from the old snapshot-only bead)
1. Run tests **without** blessing to see failures:
   ```bash
   cargo test -p ftui-demo-showcase
   ```
2. Review each failing snapshot diff and verify intent.
3. Bless snapshots:
   ```bash
   BLESS=1 cargo test -p ftui-demo-showcase
   ```
4. Re-run to confirm green.

### Snapshot Targets
- Dashboard screen
- Chrome elements (tab bar, status bar)
- Visual effects (if deterministic)
- Any screen with layout changes

### Determinism Notes
- Seed RNG for effects where necessary.
- Avoid time-based instability in snapshots.

---

## E2E Script & Logging Standard

Create/extend `scripts/demo_showcase_e2e.sh` with:
- Timestamped log dir (`/tmp/ftui_demo_e2e_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS`)
- Environment dump (`TERM`, `COLORTERM`, `NO_COLOR`, size)
- Full stdout/stderr capture
- Pass/fail summary with exit codes

---

## Debug Logging Hooks

Feature-gate render diagnostics so we can trace visual regressions:
```rust
